      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T10:40:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We don’t actually need an extra thread to integrate Boost.Asio with sdbusplus. It’s entirely possible to run both Boost’s io_context and sdbusplus APIs together under a single event loop using C++20 coroutines. This pattern already works in practice—for example, bmc-pairing-manager uses Boost.Asio coroutines alongside sdbusplus without any additional threading overhead:\nhttps://github.com/ibm-openbmc/bmc-pairing-manager/blob/main/src/provisioningd.cpp\nSo the concern about mandatory extra threads or event-loop bridging doesn’t hold for this use‑case.",
      "parentUuid": "198b1563_29b222be",
      "revId": "c2873f82fb4e7c2b609a49ba290b5222fd934ff8",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
